22/01/2003
BELGRADE, Yugoslavia -- Macedonian Assembly Chairman Nikola Popovski and his Yugoslav counterpart, Dragoljub Micunovic, met in Belgrade Tuesday (21 January) and agreed to intensify economic and political contacts as well as cultural ties between their countries.
They also agreed on a common approach towards issues related to Euro-Atlantic integration.
In Skopje meanwhile, the military announced that ten Macedonian officers will join the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan at the end of February.
The unit will replace two Macedonian officers currently there and will serve under the German contingent.
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 22/01/03;
MIA, Makfax - 21/01/03)
